steps.description: Add a tablespoon of butter to a medium hot pat, when it begins to sizzle, add the onions. When the onions begin to turn brown, add the worchester sauce and continue cooking until the onions are sticky and jam-like then set aside and clean the pan.
Season the meat with salt and pepper then sear on very high heat to get maximum color. If the pan is not super hot the meat will boil. When done, set aside and clean the pan.
Scramble the eggs and fold into an omellete like shape then top with cheese.

stepSections.name: Toast the Buns, Assemble, and Serve
